  <element name="Ranged Precision" type="Class Feature" source="GM Binder SW5E" id="ID_GMBINDER_SW5E_CLASS_FEATURE_SENTINEL_RANGED_PERCICISON">
		<description>
			<p>Additionally at level 5, you have learned how to use the force to influence your precise aim. When you make a ranged weapon attack, your disadvantage range equals the weapon's effective range. The only disadvantage you take on ranged weapons is within the close disadvantage range.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet>
		<description>When you make a ranged weapon attack, your disadvantage range equals the weapon's effective range. The only disadvantage you take on ranged weapons is within the close disadvantage range.</description>
		</sheet>
			<rules />
	</element>

  <element name="Lightsaber Control" type="Class Feature" source="GM Binder SW5E" id="ID_GMBINDER_SW5E_CLASS_FEATURE_SENTINEL_LIGHTSABER_CONTROL">
		<description>
			<p>Starting at level 7, you have mastered the art of controlling your lightsaber without physically wielding it.</p>
      <p class="indent">You can now use the Throw action on your turn, as shown on the Lightsaber stat block below. Additionally, as an action on your turn, you can use 3 force points to start controlling your lightsaber. When you do so, your lightsaber gains all the properties listed in the Lightsaber stat block below. You control its movement on your turn, and can have it perform one of its action as your bonus action.</p>
      <p class="indent">If your lightsaber's HP is reduced to zero, it is broken, and thus can no longer be used. You must use a short rest to repair it.</p>
      <p class="indent">At the beginning of your next turn, the Lightsaber returns to your hand unless you choose to use 2 force points to extend the duration.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet usage="Bonus Action">
		<description>You can now throw your lightsaber on your turn, as shown on the Lightsaber stat block below. Additionally, as an action on your turn, you can use 3 force points to start controlling your lightsaber. When you do so, your lightsaber gains all the properties listed in the Lightsaber stat block below. You control its movement on your turn, and can have it perform one of its action as your bonus action.</description>
		</sheet>
			<rules>
				<select type="Companion" name="Senator’s Companion" supports="Humanoid,Medium,1/2" />
				<stat name="companion:ac" value="0" />
				<stat name="companion:attack" value="0" />
				<stat name="companion:damage" value="0" />
				<stat name="additional:hp:max" value="0" />
				<stat name="additional:hp:max" value="0" />
				<stat name="additional:hp:max" value="0" />
				<stat name="additional:hp:max" value="0" />
				<stat name="companion:hp:max" value="additional:hp:max" bonus="base" />
			</rules>
	</element>

  <element name="Force Shield" type="Class Feature" source="GM Binder SW5E" id="ID_GMBINDER_SW5E_CLASS_FEATURE_SENTINEL_FORCE_SHIELD">
		<description>
			<p>Beginning at 9th level, you have learned to channel the force into a protective shield. As a free action on your turn, you can use 1-3 force points to give yourself 1d10 per force point spent temporary HP.</p>
      <p class="indent">From level 17 onwards you can use up to 5 force points on this ability.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet action="Free Action">
		<description>You can use 1-{{force-shield:max}} force points to give yourself 1d10 per force point spent temporary HP.</description>
		</sheet>
			<rules>
        <stat name="force-shield:max" value="3" />
        <stat name="force-shield:max" value="2" level="17" />

        <stat name="calculation" value="force-shield:max" bonus="calculation" />
      </rules>
	</element>

  <element name="Battle Meditation" type="Class Feature" source="GM Binder SW5E" id="ID_GMBINDER_SW5E_CLASS_FEATURE_SENTINEL_BATTLE_MEDITATION">
		<description>
			<p>At level 13, a sentinel learns the proper way to meditate before a battle to gain the advantage. You can spend 2 minutes before entering combat to give up to six friendly creatures temporary hit points equal to your sentinel level plus your Intelligence modifier. Once this ability has been used you cannot use it again until you have completed a long rest.</p>
		</description>
		<sheet>
		<description>You can spend 2 minutes before entering combat to give up to six friendly creatures temporary hit points equal to {{battle-meditation:sentinel}}.</description>
		</sheet>
			<rules>
        <stat name="battle-meditation:level" value="Level" />
        <stat name="battle-meditation:intelligence" value="inelligence:modifier" />

        <stat name="battle-meditation:sentinel" value="battle-meditation:level" />
        <stat name="battle-meditation:sentinel" value="battle-meditation:intelligence" />

        <stat name="calculation" value="battle-meditation:sentinel" bonus="calculation" />
